About Me

My Journey

From Education to Passions

I am dedicated to bringing justice to people and protecting nature and culture. My education consisted on understanding the intersectionality between, people, their relationship to the natural world, and the impacts of injustice against both. This deep connection between the two is what drives me for the protection of both, it is a special relationship, and both the rights of humans and of nature must be protected.

With a flexible and adaptable personality, I can navigate myself through any setting and overcome any problem. I bring an approachable presence but a passionate drive for justice and change. Outside of my professional work I love to read, study languages, and garden.
